### CREATE THE POST

> cd ~/myblog
> hugo new posts/my-new-post.md
> Change the front matter
> Write the post
> Preview locally
    >hugo server > Click localhost link

### TELL GIT TO WHICH FILES YOU WANT TO INCLUDE IN THE NEXT COMMIT

> git add content/posts/my-new-post.md


### COMMIT THE CHANGE
> git commit -m "Add new post"
# -m means "message"

### PUSH THE CHANGE
git push


### 
Think of GitHub + Hugo as a “build-and-publish machine”:

Write → local files only

git add → mark files to include

git commit → snapshot for the machine

git push → send snapshot to GitHub

GitHub Actions → rebuild site → live HTML

Visitors see the new post
###


